latticelm
------------------------------------------
This is a program to learn a word-based language model from a collection of
sentences or lattices. It uses non-parametric Bayesian techniques, specifically
the Pitman-Yor language model, to find a good segmentation.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libfst7-1.6.2-1bl1
  libgcc1-6.4.0-5
  libstdc++6-6.4.0-5

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.0-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-5
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-5
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.phontron.com/latticelm/

Canonical download:
  http://www.phontron.com/latticelm/download/latticelm-0.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack latticelm-0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./latticelm-0.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/latticelm-0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/latticelm-0.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(latticelm)
  /usr/bin/latticelm.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/latticelm.README
  /usr/share/doc/latticelm/README

------------------

